h6.Summary
When a team member assigned to an issue in Portfolio was renamed, applying the updates to JIRA project will fail.

h6.Steps to reproduce

# Create a JIRA Portfolio plan and import issues;
# in the *People* section, create a team and add a JIRA user to it;
# assign an issue to a user in the _Members_ column;
# go to *User Management* and rename the user selected in previous step;
# in Portfolio, click *Plan > Apply updates to project/s* and then *Update* in the displayed dialog.

*Expected result:* issues are updated normally.
*Actual result:*
- in the _Update linked elements_ notification after the update attempt, *Show Details* link will display the warnings, with an error message: "User '...' does not exist", referring to the old username;
- in JIRA, the edited issue isn't updated;
- errors are thrown in JIRA logs:
{noformat}
@4000000054fd67990da5762c 2015-03-09 09:27:43,228 TP-Processor9 WARN dwierzbicka 567x463x1 1syk3vh 46.243.25.78,59.167.29.201 /rest/roadmap/1.0/plans/1/sync.json [common.components.utils.JiraErrorCollectionUtil] assignee: User 'ABC' does not exist.
{noformat}

*Workaround:* rename the user back to the original name.

