Best I can tell from reading the doco, the current Themes functionality assumes that all themes belong to the same set. I.e. they're non-overlapping at the leaf nodes of the WBS *and* they all make sense to go on a single pie-chart.
I have a need to create two sets of themes: one set relating to the customer domains I'm serving (e.g. logistics, finance, medical) and another set relating to the strategic objectives I'm serving (e.g. consolidate base, develop new capability, grow revenue). I would want to report Target/Estimate/Actual of these two sets on separate pie charts.
I suggest that the Themes functionality be extended to allow orthogonal sets of themes to be defined, allocated to Stories and then reported.

